Filer: Legendary boxing trainer, Mzimasi Mnguni has died at the age of 72. (eNCA) JOHANNESBURG - Boxing icon, Mzimasi Mnguni, will be laid to rest this weekend. The late Bra Mzi has been afforded a Provincial state funeral category two and is set to have two services. The first one will be held this morning at the Presbyterian Church of Southern Africa in Gompo. READ:Â SA boxing legend Mzimasi Mnguni dies aged 72 The burial service will be held at his home village, eMaZotshweni in Alice tomorrow. Mnguni died last weekend following a long illness. Known as a trainer, promoter and manager, he produced a number of world and national champions in boxing.